But according to psychology

00:00:23.106 --> 00:00:25.817
it's due to the Zeigarnik effect.

00:00:26.234 --> 00:00:28.445
The Zeigarnik effect

00:00:28.445 --> 00:00:30.196
is when we can't easily

00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:33.199
let go of things that feel incomplete.

00:00:33.199 --> 00:00:37.579
A good example is when you're watching
a drama and it ends on a cliffhanger.

00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:41.249
You can't wait to see what happens next.

00:00:46.129 --> 00:00:49.841
If someone is struggling
to get over their first love

00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:53.344
how about using
the Zeigarnik effect to your advantage?

00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:58.099
Tell yourself, "It's over"
"Goodbye"

00:00:58.516 --> 00:01:00.852
to close that chapter of your life

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:03.938
so you don't have any regrets.

