The expression we’ll be
learning today is "nakereba naranai."

00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:36.024
[Hello, Japanese Lesson]
This means "must"

00:29:36.691 --> 00:29:39.819
but lots of you hear "nakereba naranai"

00:29:39.819 --> 00:29:42.739
and think that it means "should"

00:29:42.739 --> 00:29:47.285
but it doesn't match
the meaning of the Korean word

00:29:47.285 --> 00:29:49.370
so nakereba naranai...

00:29:52.999 --> 00:29:54.959
Kang Hana, you must be crazy.

00:30:38.294 --> 00:30:39.504
Mom.

00:30:40.213 --> 00:30:41.798
I'm going to school.

00:30:41.798 --> 00:30:45.301
Wow, you put your hair down?

00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:48.930
Oh, yeah...

00:30:49.639 --> 00:30:52.767
Great job, my daughter.

00:30:53.101 --> 00:30:54.561
You look so pretty.

00:30:56.813 --> 00:30:58.273
I'll be back.

00:30:58.731 --> 00:31:00.567
Have fun, princess.

