Yeah, I'm fine.

00:42:24.792 --> 00:42:26.293
This won't do.

00:42:27.002 --> 00:42:28.379
Let's sit down for a bit.

00:42:47.773 --> 00:42:49.441
Do you pity me?

00:42:50.943 --> 00:42:52.486
Is that why you said that?

00:42:53.279 --> 00:42:55.531
What do you mean?

00:42:56.532 --> 00:43:01.036
Why did you say you were my boyfriend?

00:43:02.413 --> 00:43:04.290
You aren't.

00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:08.127
That's because...

00:43:09.336 --> 00:43:10.921
I don't know either.

00:43:14.383 --> 00:43:20.264
I just couldn't bear to see them
talking bad about you.

00:43:22.558 --> 00:43:26.103
I more than deserve it, so...

00:43:26.145 --> 00:43:27.771
Why would you say that?

00:43:30.441 --> 00:43:32.359
Because Haeri is right.

00:43:32.985 --> 00:43:35.404
I asked you to keep it a secret

00:43:36.071 --> 00:43:38.741
because I was scared people might
find out about my disabled mom.

00:43:38.741 --> 00:43:42.286
Stupid, stupid.

00:43:42.286 --> 00:43:44.413
My mom's not stupid!

00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:47.124
She's not stupid!

00:43:47.791 --> 00:43:51.003
Ma'am, you need to pay 1,700 won
not 1,500 won.

00:43:51.003 --> 00:43:52.379
No...

00:43:52.379 --> 00:43:56.133
It's 1,700 won by card
and 1,500 won with cash.

00:43:56.133 --> 00:43:57.635
I got it right.

00:43:59.345 --> 00:44:01.221
Hurry and pay 200 won more.

00:44:01.221 --> 00:44:06.226
No, it's 1,700 won by card
and 1,500 won with cash!

00:44:06.226 --> 00:44:08.228
I paid the right price...

00:44:10.022 --> 00:44:12.983
What? How could she confuse the two?

00:44:12.983 --> 00:44:14.276
What's wrong with her?

00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:21.325
Every day is hell for me.

00:44:24.078 --> 00:44:28.248
I wonder why my dad married my mom.

00:44:29.708 --> 00:44:32.378
If he was going to die
without taking responsibility for her

00:44:34.088 --> 00:44:36.298
he shouldn't have married her.

00:44:37.841 --> 00:44:40.302
That's why I hated that coin.

00:44:42.304 --> 00:44:44.556
If it weren't for that coin

00:44:46.558 --> 00:44:48.686
my parents wouldn't have met

00:44:51.021 --> 00:44:53.565
and I wouldn't have been born.

00:44:57.736 --> 00:44:59.405
So...

00:45:26.265 --> 00:45:27.641
Hana.

00:45:29.476 --> 00:45:30.894
Don't beat yourself up.

00:45:33.981 --> 00:45:36.608
Anyone would've done what you did.

00:45:39.611 --> 00:45:42.281
You're different now.

00:45:42.281 --> 00:45:45.743
You say you don't like your mom

00:45:45.743 --> 00:45:48.078
but you study hard for her.

00:45:50.289 --> 00:45:53.167
And didn't you want to
make it big for your mom?

00:45:56.587 --> 00:46:02.259
From what I've seen
you love your mom.

00:46:25.324 --> 00:46:27.242
Thanks for walking me home.

00:46:27.868 --> 00:46:29.411
Have a safe trip back.

00:46:33.165 --> 00:46:34.666
Hana.

00:46:36.335 --> 00:46:38.378
The kids are worried for you.

00:46:39.713 --> 00:46:43.383
I really hope you come to school tomorrow.

00:46:47.304 --> 00:46:48.806
Good night.

00:46:50.766 --> 00:46:52.100
Bye.

00:47:11.578 --> 00:47:13.288
[Seulgi]
We need your electronic whistle.

00:47:13.288 --> 00:47:15.082
The classroom is a mess.

00:47:15.082 --> 00:47:16.834
Come back.

00:47:16.834 --> 00:47:19.753
[Sunwoo]
Hana, hurry up and come back.

00:47:19.753 --> 00:47:22.339
I'm trying to do your part too
and my head has been killing me.

00:47:43.610 --> 00:47:46.738
What's going on?
Why are you here?

00:47:47.948 --> 00:47:50.117
You hurt your foot.

00:47:52.327 --> 00:47:55.163
No, I'm okay.

00:47:55.414 --> 00:47:57.583
You still have to be careful for today.

00:47:59.126 --> 00:48:00.794
Here, get on.

00:48:03.505 --> 00:48:06.049
If you don't get on, I'm not going.

00:48:06.925 --> 00:48:08.844
Geez.

00:48:19.021 --> 00:48:20.981
Hana, hold onto me.

00:48:25.861 --> 00:48:27.529
Alright, here we go.

00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:37.164
To be honest
I didn't think you'd come today.

00:48:37.164 --> 00:48:41.919
After crying it out yesterday
I suddenly felt okay.

00:48:43.045 --> 00:48:46.882
You saw me at my lowest point
but it was okay.

00:48:48.008 --> 00:48:49.468
It's so cool.

00:48:49.468 --> 00:48:51.011
Do you know why?

00:48:51.845 --> 00:48:53.347
It's because we're friends.

00:49:05.400 --> 00:49:07.653
[Life Four Cuts]

00:49:11.156 --> 00:49:12.574
This is great.

00:49:21.833 --> 00:49:22.918
How cute.

00:49:22.918 --> 00:49:24.294
It's not cute.

00:49:24.753 --> 00:49:26.129
You look great, Hana.

00:49:26.129 --> 00:49:27.923
You too.

00:49:28.215 --> 00:49:29.591
You're good at posing.

00:49:29.591 --> 00:49:31.385
Let's take one each.

00:49:31.927 --> 00:49:34.221
Huh? Why?

00:49:34.221 --> 00:49:36.932
I heard Korean couples do that.

00:49:37.599 --> 00:49:38.767
Huh?

00:49:40.477 --> 00:49:45.649
Yeah, but we're not a real couple.

00:49:47.025 --> 00:49:49.569
Still, we're a couple.

00:49:51.613 --> 00:49:53.490
Oh, Hana. Hold on.

00:49:55.117 --> 00:49:56.660
Mitsuha, hold on.

00:50:01.915 --> 00:50:03.375
Mitsuha?

00:50:04.042 --> 00:50:07.170
[I wish Mitsuha stays healthy]

00:50:08.630 --> 00:50:11.174
Is that your girlfriend's wish?

00:50:12.050 --> 00:50:13.427
Mitsuha.

00:50:15.178 --> 00:50:19.224
You sound healthy.
I'm glad.

00:50:20.559 --> 00:50:22.769
Of course I miss you.

00:50:23.687 --> 00:50:26.940
I'm gonna go see you right away
when I get back to Japan.

00:50:27.566 --> 00:50:31.069
I bought a bunch of things
you like, so you just wait.

00:50:31.278 --> 00:50:33.488
I thought you didn't have a girlfriend.

00:50:35.198 --> 00:50:36.491
Cheater.

00:50:41.788 --> 00:50:43.123
Hana!

00:50:44.458 --> 00:50:45.751
Hana!

00:50:49.796 --> 00:50:51.089
Hana!

00:50:54.468 --> 00:50:56.928
Hana, what's wrong?

00:50:57.971 --> 00:50:59.848
I suddenly got a reality check.

00:51:01.016 --> 00:51:02.684
I'm worried I'll fail my finals

00:51:02.684 --> 00:51:05.062
if I keep hanging around with you.

00:51:09.399 --> 00:51:11.151
I'm gonna go study.

00:51:12.986 --> 00:51:15.363
Oh, sorry.

00:51:17.032 --> 00:51:19.159
I didn't think about that.

00:51:21.995 --> 00:51:24.331
Did I use up too much of your time?

00:51:27.751 --> 00:51:28.960
Yes.

00:51:36.009 --> 00:51:37.552
But I'll still

00:51:40.097 --> 00:51:42.349
help you out at school as your guide.

00:51:45.644 --> 00:51:46.937
Bye.

00:52:57.424 --> 00:53:00.385
Hikari, if you like her, confess.

00:53:01.344 --> 00:53:04.306
She might become your first love.

00:53:04.639 --> 00:53:08.518
I can't confess just because I like her.

00:53:08.977 --> 00:53:13.523
I don't want to confess
without considering how Hana feels.

00:53:13.857 --> 00:53:17.444
Dummy. Confessions are one-sided.

00:53:17.861 --> 00:53:21.406
It's just a matter of
whether she accepts your feelings or not.

00:53:21.406 --> 00:53:26.661
If you don't tell her how you feel
I'm sure you'll regret it.

00:53:29.956 --> 00:53:31.499
I'm worried I'll fail my finals

00:53:31.499 --> 00:53:33.752
if I keep hanging around with you.

00:53:36.671 --> 00:53:40.592
But I don't want to overwhelm her.

00:53:42.177 --> 00:53:46.848
Studying is more important to her
than dating right now.

00:53:46.848 --> 00:53:47.933
Dummy.

00:53:49.309 --> 00:53:52.604
I have to go get a checkup.
Let's talk later.

00:54:24.177 --> 00:54:27.597
[Two: Making a wish on Milmiri Bridge]

00:54:29.307 --> 00:54:32.811
[Four: Going to the set of
Guardian: The Lonely and Great God]

00:54:36.189 --> 00:54:40.026
[Five: Taking a Life Four Cut]

00:54:43.363 --> 00:54:47.117
[Six: Visiting the birthplace
of Heo Nanseolheon]

00:55:13.268 --> 00:55:16.146
[End of being a guide]

00:55:22.736 --> 00:55:25.488
Alright, before we take the picture

00:55:25.905 --> 00:55:28.908
- Hikari should say a word.
- Okay.

00:55:33.121 --> 00:55:37.167
Thank you so much for organizing
such an amazing farewell party.

00:55:37.167 --> 00:55:39.336
What's wrong with you?
You don't have to use honorifics!

00:55:39.336 --> 00:55:41.963
Guys, listen. Let's hear him out.

00:55:41.963 --> 00:55:43.798
Guys, let's hear him out.

00:55:44.674 --> 00:55:49.596
Your kindness and friendships
already made me incredibly happy.

00:55:50.055 --> 00:55:53.141
I'll never be able to forget the month
I spent here at Soorim High.

00:55:53.475 --> 00:55:54.726
Thank you.

00:55:55.435 --> 00:55:59.064
So, hit me up if you ever come to Japan.

00:55:59.731 --> 00:56:01.149
I'll be your guide.

00:56:04.069 --> 00:56:06.279
I'm going to take full advantage of that!

00:56:06.279 --> 00:56:08.198
Be quiet.
Let's take the photo.

00:56:09.199 --> 00:56:11.284
- Stick together!
- Guys, get closer.

00:56:13.203 --> 00:56:14.913
One, two, three!

00:56:15.372 --> 00:56:18.625
One, two, three!
Okay.

00:56:21.628 --> 00:56:23.213
Hikari.

00:56:23.963 --> 00:56:25.632
I actually

00:56:25.965 --> 00:56:30.720
wanted to ask you why you were
so nice to me when you had a girlfriend.

00:56:35.475 --> 00:56:37.644
But I thought about it

00:56:38.186 --> 00:56:40.605
and I didn't have the right to ask you.

00:56:44.234 --> 00:56:46.277
I'm nothing

00:56:46.277 --> 00:56:50.573
but an exchange student's guide to you.

00:56:52.367 --> 00:56:54.411
I'm sorry I couldn't

00:56:54.994 --> 00:57:00.333
leave you with good memories
because I got frustrated.

00:57:12.929 --> 00:57:14.597
Alright, let's get the classroom ready.

00:57:14.597 --> 00:57:15.849
- Tae-woong? Where are you going?
- Nowhere.

00:57:17.934 --> 00:57:21.771
I'll be okay, I'll be okay...

00:57:24.524 --> 00:57:26.025
Give this to Hikari.

00:57:27.444 --> 00:57:31.364
He said his sister was a fan
so I asked Bong-hee

00:57:31.364 --> 00:57:33.575
but I've been holding onto it
because I didn't like you guys.

00:57:34.576 --> 00:57:37.454
But his little sister is sick, so here.

00:57:38.872 --> 00:57:40.248
His sister?

00:57:40.748 --> 00:57:44.669
Yeah, Hikari's bucket list
was actually his little sister's.

00:57:44.878 --> 00:57:46.379
Anyway, you should give it to him.

00:57:51.468 --> 00:57:52.886
[TO: Mitsuha]
[Pa-ran]

00:57:52.927 --> 00:57:54.762
[Good luck on your surgery]
[I'll be cheering you on from Korea]

00:57:56.306 --> 00:57:58.057
It was his sister?

00:58:10.904 --> 00:58:12.197
Hikari!

00:58:17.869 --> 00:58:19.162
Hana.

00:58:22.916 --> 00:58:25.418
Haeri asked me to give this to you.

00:58:28.254 --> 00:58:29.547
Thanks.

00:58:29.839 --> 00:58:31.508
Mitsuha will love it.

00:58:32.383 --> 00:58:36.721
Why didn't you tell me
it was your sister's bucket list?

00:58:37.597 --> 00:58:39.182
Because...

00:58:41.559 --> 00:58:45.772
I thought you'd feel obligated
if I told you it was for my sick sister.

00:58:51.903 --> 00:58:56.616
You did everything
on that bucket list, right?

00:58:57.075 --> 00:58:58.451
Yes, thanks to you.

00:59:01.579 --> 00:59:02.872
Thanks.

00:59:06.417 --> 00:59:11.589
I'll pray for your sister's health.

00:59:13.049 --> 00:59:15.927
You have to stay healthy too.

00:59:18.221 --> 00:59:19.514
Okay.

00:59:20.974 --> 00:59:22.350
Hana.

00:59:24.602 --> 00:59:27.689
I like you.

00:59:29.899 --> 00:59:31.776
I'll miss you.

00:59:35.280 --> 00:59:38.408
Study hard and become a doctor.

00:59:40.577 --> 00:59:41.744
Okay.

00:59:45.957 --> 00:59:47.250
Then...

00:59:50.003 --> 00:59:51.504
Goodbye.

01:00:28.249 --> 01:00:30.293
Dude, you're basically
inviting in mosquitoes.

01:00:33.296 --> 01:00:34.839
Hikari asked me to give this to you.

01:00:35.632 --> 01:00:36.799
Huh?

01:00:39.302 --> 01:00:40.595
Thanks.

01:00:55.485 --> 01:00:57.403
[To Hana]

01:00:57.403 --> 01:01:00.740
To Hana, who helped me during
my month as an exchange student.

01:01:01.658 --> 01:01:04.077
Thanks to you, I was happy in Korea.

01:01:04.952 --> 01:01:07.914
I'll miss you a lot
once I return to Japan.

01:01:09.290 --> 01:01:11.668
I'll especially miss
seeing you study hard.

01:01:13.086 --> 01:01:16.881
Let's both work hard
and get into the universities we want.

01:01:18.341 --> 01:01:20.009
And if you get into Seoul University

01:01:20.009 --> 01:01:22.261
you have to come to Japan
to return the omamori.

01:01:23.554 --> 01:01:25.765
If you don't, the gods will get angry.

01:01:27.475 --> 01:01:31.813
And the Japanese coin
is a present for you.

01:01:33.439 --> 01:01:38.027
In Japan, the five-yen coin is called
the coin of fate, or a lucky coin.

01:01:39.612 --> 01:01:43.324
"Go-en" sounds similar
to the Japanese word that means fate

01:01:43.324 --> 01:01:46.619
and they say luck comes and goes
through the hole in the coin.

01:01:47.745 --> 01:01:49.872
I hope you take all the luck.

01:01:50.331 --> 01:01:53.543
I wish you all the best of luck.
Sato Hikari.

01:02:15.857 --> 01:02:18.317
To me, first love

01:02:18.568 --> 01:02:22.238
is the feeling I never got to confess.

01:02:43.760 --> 01:02:46.637
[First Love]

01:02:46.888 --> 01:02:50.433
How would you feel if the person you liked
was in love with someone else?

01:02:50.433 --> 01:02:52.560
How about you? Tell me.

01:03:00.943 --> 01:03:03.863
- Are you crazy? Hey!
- Stop it! Hey!

01:03:03.863 --> 01:03:05.406
Do you have an inferiority complex?

01:03:05.406 --> 01:03:06.699
Why!

01:03:06.699 --> 01:03:08.159
[Nam Hao]

01:03:12.830 --> 01:03:14.207
What are you doing?

01:03:15.291 --> 01:03:16.667
Just get lost!

01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:17.794
You're so annoying.

01:03:19.337 --> 01:03:22.673
The guy who claims to be my dad's son
showed up at our house.

01:03:22.673 --> 01:03:24.425
These two are brothers.

01:03:24.926 --> 01:03:27.470
Every day is like hell because I'm scared
people will find out we're brothers!

01:03:29.597 --> 01:03:31.098
He went international, huh?